	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=278938><span id= >ryunotao</span></a><br><span id=notbold>85 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [2.80]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>Okay...&nbsp;&nbsp;I'm going against the current on this one.<br><br>A lot of players want WR bags, and a lot of players can't afford to spend 5k on a 100% WR bag.<br><br>A nice alternative is 1-2k on one of these bags.  It's an upgrade to the lemming fur ones.  I just sold two, really easily in an /ooc at the bazaar for 1500 each.  Bearing in mind failures, granted, I probably should have sold them for 1750+.  <br><br>At any rate, I will say only two negatives on this:<br>as of the date of this post, August 6th... The bag exchange doesn't support these.  No tokens yet (It says try back in the future).  <br><br>I don't like the icon graphic for it as much as i do the haversack-type icon.<br><br>As for the farming of the rallic packs, I'd call that a ridiculous waste of time.  They're lore, as mentioned below, so you're gunna do those one at a time.  A quest is involved, and you gotta run way out in the boonies to do it.  Last but not least, I can get hard-to-find skill ups on this bag, which trivials at 202.  Tailoring is a tough skill.  As long as folks will buy this bag, it's worth it for me.  Heck, I'll upgrade my own lemming furs with it as soon as I can afford to not sell a few.<br><br><em id=fs8>Edited, Fri Aug  6 08:10:46 2004</em></p>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
