	     <tr><td id=headerrow colspan=2 class=mform valign=top><a name=/db/item.html?item=27052&mid=10869620704256>&nbsp;</a><a id=sj href=/db/item.html?item=27052&mid=10869620704256>Too Much, Too Little</a> <a id=fs8 href=/db/item.html?item=27052&mid=10869620704256#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a>
	     <br clear=all><small>Posted @ Fri, Jun 11th 9:54 AM 2004</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=210061><span id=Scholar>jhoward</span></a><br><b><span id=Scholar>Scholar</span></b><br><span id=notbold>33 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [3.33]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>Well folks in my own opinion, this bag, while a very nice upgrade to the handmade backpack, is way too much trouble and way too expensive to make for what you get.<br><br>The shimmering steel threads are purchased in The Abysmal Sea for betwwen 50-65 plat each, depending on your race and charisma level, and you need 5 threads per pack. Your cost so far, and I'm using minimum prices, 250 plat. Bear in mind that 10% WR Handmade Backpacks sell for around 50 plat each.<br><br>You will need 1 High Quality Hynid Hide, and 5 Hynid bloods. Both are very uncommon drops in Natimbi. I was there for 2 hours and got 1 of each. You also need 5 Tea Leaf oils, which are foraged, and more on the uncommon side to get.<br><br>So unless you are willing to spend a lot of time foraging and farming Hynid bloods and hides you have another option...The Bazaar!<br><br>Tea Leaf Oil runs about 1-5 plat each. You need 5 Oils for another minimum of 5 plat.<br>Hynid Blood runs between 75-1500 plat each (remember it's the bazaar.) You need 5 of those for another 375 plat.<br>High Quality Hynid Hides average about 250 plat each.<br><br>So you can either farm your life away and make them for about 300 plat each, or you can buy what you need and crank them out for around 650 plat each. Either way you have a nice giant size, 10 slot, 30% WR bag.<br><br>Or you can go to Tennebrous Mountains and kill the runner and make Rallic Packs for about 0 plat each, spend about an hour doing it, and end up with a giant size, 10 slot, 85% WR bag. You can also sell the Rallic Packs for a sweet profit of 700-1000 plat. I wouldn't pay anywhere near 650 for the Hynid packs, but that's me.<br>However, the Rallic Packs are lore and the Hynid packs are not. Just my 2 cents worth. </p>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
